Hi Josh,
All you need to do is remove old (1500?) P&Cs and install new 1600 P&Cs.  
While you are at it, it would be nice to install a CW crank, have the FW balanced 
to the crank and balance the rods and pistons.  Really makes for a smooth 
running engine!
